The paper focuses on online learning using deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning subfield. Specifically, the paper discusses the generalization abilities of Lipschitz regularized deep neural networks in nonparametric online learning tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also touches on control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.LO) in the context of online learning, which are less likely but still relevant sub-categories.
